 as the complete source of truth for every food element shown\r\n- rearrange, restage, and elevate the ingredients from the uploaded dish into a more premium commercial composition\r\n- keep the final image clearly recognizable as the same menu from the uploaded food image, not a different dish\r\n- preserve the real ingredients, cooking style, colors, textures, proportions, and identity of the uploaded dish\r\n- do not invent new side dishes, sauces, herbs, chilies, or garnishes unless they are clearly present in the uploaded food image\r\n- every visible food element must come from or be strongly supported by the uploaded dish\r\n\r\nComposition:\r\n- vertical premium food-poster framing similar to the reference\r\n- dark matte tabletop or slate-like serving surface\r\n- hero food arranged diagonally across the lower-middle to center area\r\n- supporting edible elements placed around the hero item in a refined and balanced way\r\n- shallow depth of field with softly blurred background food elements near the top\r\n- tight, appetizing framing with strong focus on texture and gloss\r\n- clean premium commercial composition with controlled negative space\r\n\r\nFood styling requirements:\r\n- transform the uploaded dish into a dramatic high-end styled presentation while staying faithful to the original menu\r\n- use the major visible ingredients from the uploaded dish throughout the final arrangement whenever naturally possible\r\n- if the uploaded dish includes sauce, dips, toppings, garnish, or side elements, they may be restaged into small premium supporting placements\r\n- if the uploaded dish does not include certain side elements, do not add them\r\n- preserve realistic texture, sauce gloss, char, crispness, moisture, fibers, and surface detail\r\n- make the food look rich, juicy, hot, appetizing, and professionally photographed\r\n- do not oversmooth the food\r\n- do not make it look fake, plastic, or AI-polished\r\n\r\nLighting and mood requirements:\r\n- mat