 arranged neatly on the plate only if supported by the uploaded image\r\n- make the food look realistic, premium, fresh, and professionally photographed\r\n- preserve realistic moisture, gloss, crispness, sauce detail, fibers, char, and natural surface texture where appropriate\r\n- do not oversmooth the food\r\n- do not make it look fake, plastic, or overly polished\r\n\r\nCloche and smoke requirements:\r\n- keep a clear glass cloche being lifted above the dish\r\n- the cloche should look elegant, realistic, and transparent with natural reflections\r\n- create abundant cinematic smoke swirling around and above the plate\r\n- smoke should feel soft, layered, and natural, not artificial or fog-machine heavy\r\n- keep the smoke as a dramatic visual element, but do not let it fully hide the dish\r\n- the reveal moment should feel premium, theatrical, and refined\r\n\r\nLighting and mood requirements:\r\n- match the reference image’s dark dramatic fine-dining mood\r\n- strong directional studio lighting focused on the plate, smoke, and cloche\r\n- deep black shadows with soft highlight transitions\r\n- realistic reflections on the glass cloche\r\n- subtle glow and contrast on the food surface\r\n- overall tone should feel elegant, mysterious, luxurious, and high-end\r\n\r\nStyling constraints:\r\n- keep the scene minimal and clean\r\n- no extra props unless naturally required by the plated presentation\r\n- no unrelated cutlery, bottles, napkins, or table items\r\n- keep the focus on the food, smoke, and cloche reveal\r\n- composition should feel commercially usable and visually refined\r\n\r\nImportant constraints:\r\n- absolutely no text, captions, slogans, labels, logos, watermarks, or typography anywhere in the image\r\n- no extra dishes\r\n- no fake ingredients not supported by the uploaded food image\r\n- no messy composition\r\n- no collage layout\r\n- no cartoon look\r\n- no distorted hand, cloche, plate, smoke, or food anatomy\r\n\r\nStyle direction:\r\npremium