ploaded food image\r\n- preserve the exact identity of the uploaded dish\r\n- do not redesign or reinterpret it into another menu\r\n- keep the real ingredients, colors, textures, proportions, plating character, and recognizable appearance of the uploaded dish\r\n- restage the food naturally into a refined premium plated presentation inspired by the reference\r\n- if the uploaded dish includes garnish, sauce, or side elements, they may be arranged neatly only if supported by the uploaded image\r\n- make the food look realistic, premium, appetizing, and professionally photographed\r\n- preserve realistic gloss, moisture, crispness, fibers, sauce detail, and natural shadow depth\r\n- do not oversmooth the food\r\n- do not make it look fake or plastic\r\n\r\nTypography concept:\r\n- replace all existing text in the reference with a completely new Thai typography composition\r\n- use Thai language only for all visible text unless the user explicitly inputs another language\r\n- design the typography from scratch as bespoke Thai composition typography, not a standard font overlay\r\n- create a new custom typographic composition every time based on the exact input words\r\n- redesign the Thai letterforms, spacing, line breaks, proportions, hierarchy, stroke rhythm, and graphic balance according to the real input text\r\n- adapt the typography visually to the word length, meaning, tone, and rhythm of each phrase\r\n- typography should feel art-directed, editorial, elegant, premium, and custom-made for the given words\r\n- the main text should feel like a custom Thai wordmark\r\n- the secondary text should feel like a refined supporting line\r\n- the third line should feel like a small edition mark, collection line, issue line, season line, or subtle signature line depending on the input\r\n- allow refined Thai letterform styling such as expanded spacing, tall proportions, ligature-like flow, stroke contrast, overlap, nesting, inline detailing, serif-inspired Thai construction, or restrained ornamental logic when appropriate\r\n- keep the typography readable and professionally typeset in correct Thai\r\n- prioritize correct Thai spelling, correct Thai glyph structure, and natural Thai reading flow\r\n- do not generate fake Thai glyphs\r\n- do not make the typography look like generic stock fonts\r\n- do not imitate the original English letters literally; reinterpret the same premium cover-design feeling in Thai\r\n\r\nText content:\r\n- Main text: #[ข้อความหลัก](e59088b4-541b-444a-a017-98be2d7deab6) \r\n- Secondary text: #[ข้อความรอง](8d083256-b096-4ec8-a49f-8c47fc59c0df) \r\r\n\r\nTypography layout rules:\r\n- place the main Thai title in the upper center area as the dominant typographic element\r\n- place the secondary Thai line directly below the main title in a smaller but elegant complementary style\r\n- place the third line below the secondary line as a small accent line or edition marker\r\n- redesign the whole type composition every time according to the exact input words\r\n- do not copy the original reference text literally\r\n- preserve only the premium editorial hierarchy and cover-design feeling\r\n- keep the typography visually integrated with the dark book surface, the plate, and the surrounding negative space\r\n- composition should feel calm, sophisticated, luxurious, and publication-like\r\n\r\nTypography styling direction:\r\n- custom Thai editorial display typography\r\n- premium restaurant catalog cover typography\r\n- refined, elegant, minimal, and luxurious\r\n- warm gold or muted gold typography tone similar in visual mood to the reference\r\n- the main text may be wide, elegant, contrast-led, slightly high-fashion, or stately depending on the actual phrase\r\n- the secondary text may be softer, more delicate, slightly italic-feeling in spirit, or more graceful while remaining clearly Thai\r\n- the third line may be compact, sharp, understated, and balanced\r\n- no cheap effects\r\n- no bevel\r\n- no fake metallic 3D embossing unless subtle and tasteful\r\n- no random decorative swashes unless justified by the Thai words\r\n- no placeholder English text\r\n- no Latin-looking Thai\r\n\r\nLighting and mood requirements:\r\n- match the reference image’s premium dark editorial mood\r\n- soft controlled overhead lighting on the plate\r\n- subtle highlight falloff across the dark book surface\r\n- rich shadows and elegant texture on the background\r\n- overall tone should feel luxurious, modern, calm, and high-end\r\n\r\nImportant constraints:\r\n- render only the exact text provided in the input fields\r\n- do not add extra text\r\n- do not change spelling\r\n- do not invent subtitles\r\n- remove all original reference text completely\r\n- no watermark\r\n- no logo unless explicitly provided\r\n- no extra dishes\r\n- no unrelated props\r\n- no messy layout\r\n- no distorted plate or food\r\n- no unreadable typography\r\n- no placeholder English text\r\n\r\nStyle direction:\r\npremium Thai editorial food cover, bespoke Thai composition typography, luxury restaurant catalog aesthetic, minimal high-end menu cover, custom type-led food publication design","model_name":"nano-banana-2","aspect_ratio":"3:4"},"exposed":{"prompt":false}},"type":"bananaProNode","position":{"x":360,"y":300}},{"id":"544b9a33-9692-4379-b39a-c0b779bba707","data":{"label":"Output","outputType":"video"},"type":"outputNode","position":{"x":750,"y":510}},{"id":"8fb2c46b-e1f4-4c70-ad65-c7f70218ec42","data":{"label":"Image Upload","accept":"image/*","config":{"example_image_urls":[]},"nodeName":"อาหาร1","required":true,"fieldType":"image","fieldLabel":"อาหาร"},"type":"inputNode","position":{"x":45,"y":810}},{"id":"e59088b4-541b-444a-a017-98be2d7deab6","data":{"label":"Text Input","nodeName":"ข้อความหลัก","textValue":"","fieldLabel":"ข้อความหลัก","isRequired":true,"exampleText":"NEW MENU","placeholder":"Enter text value..."},"type":"textInputNode","position":{"x":-270,"y":195}},{"id":"21c01ffd-5ef5-4fb7-bba2-d6b8c