 price badge near the lower-right area\r\n- vertical poster layout similar to the reference\r\n- premium restaurant-advertising feel\r\n- balanced hierarchy between headline, food, price,\r\n\r\nFood requirements:\r\n- replace the original dish with the uploaded food image\r\n- preserve the exact identity of the uploaded dish\r\n- do not redesign or reinterpret it into another menu\r\n- keep the real ingredients, colors, textures, proportions, and recognizable appearance of the uploaded dish\r\n- restage the food naturally into a premium promotional presentation inspired by the reference\r\n- if the uploaded dish includes garnish, broth, sauce, vegetables, or side elements, they may be arranged neatly only if supported by the uploaded image\r\n- make the dish look realistic, appetizing, premium, and professionally photographed\r\n- preserve realistic gloss, moisture, texture, crispness, sauce detail, and natural shadows\r\n- do not oversmooth the food\r\n- do not make it look fake or plastic\r\n\r\nTypography concept:\r\n- replace all existing text in the reference with a completely new Thai typography composition\r\n- use Thai language only for all visible text unless the user explicitly inputs another language\r\n- redesign all typography from scratch as bespoke Thai composition typography, not a normal stock-font overlay\r\n- create a new custom typographic arrangement every time based on the exact input words\r\n- adapt the letterforms, size, spacing, line breaks, proportions, weight, hierarchy, and graphic rhythm to the actual Thai text\r\n- the typography should feel premium, art-directed, restaurant-commercial, and custom-designed specifically for the given words\r\n- the main headline should be bold, dominant, and highly readable\r\n- the secondary line should complement the main line with its own distinct Thai display style\r\n- the price text should be clearly readable and designed to fit naturally inside the badge\r\n\nText content:\r\n- Main text: #[ข้อค