previewUrl":"https://mlbzgtoiozqztoszvkuc.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/sign/ai-media/fb4de7e2-9f6e-459b-bb1b-464f6ae14bea/3b1278af-e716-45da-9321-40447bf2bfb4.jpg?token=eyJraWQiOiJzdG9yYWdlLXVybC1zaWduaW5nLWtleV9jM2VkYzBhMy1jMDIyLTQyOTgtODIxMS1mMTc5YTA1ZDUxN2IiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJ1cmwiOiJhaS1tZWRpYS9mYjRkZTdlMi05ZjZlLTQ1OWItYmIxYi00NjRmNmFlMTRiZWEvM2IxMjc4YWYtZTcxNi00NWRhLTkzMjEtNDA0NDdiZjJiZmI0LmpwZyIsImlhdCI6MTc3NjY4NTg2OSwiZXhwIjoxNzc2NzcyMjY5fQ.r89QDQrFrYIshG_roUmMQHxZse1Y0GnH69kVFZKaObo","storagePath":"fb4de7e2-9f6e-459b-bb1b-464f6ae14bea/3b1278af-e716-45da-9321-40447bf2bfb4.jpg","creatorAsset":true},"type":"inputNode","position":{"x":-60,"y":-615}},{"id":"6bc6dde5-4cf0-4991-98b2-df0a689c05cf","data":{"label":"Banana Pro (Image Gen)","params":{"prompt":"Use two input images.\r\n\r\nImage A = @[ภาพพื้นหลัง](b874700b-e279-4442-99ff-ae642db299ac) \r\nImage B = @[ต้นแบบ](546edfae-325c-486a-9df9-9ef3f906196f) \r\n\r\nImage A is the replaceable background image and the direct edit target.\r\nImage B is the font and lettering reference image only.\r\n\r\nEdit Image A by placing new promotional typography directly on top of it.\r\nUse Image B only as a visual reference for font personality, lettering style, outline treatment, stroke thickness, slant, contrast, text decoration, and overall typography mood.\r\nDo not copy the original wording from Image B.\r\nDo not copy the text layout or exact composition from Image B.\r\nDo not use Image B as a layout reference.\r\nRemove or replace any existing overlaid text from the final design.\r\n\r\nCreate a bold, playful promotional poster using Image A as the final background.\r\nThe typography must be styled based on Image B, but arranged directly on Image A in positions that fit the background naturally and read clearly.\r\n\r\nInput text:\r\n- Line 1: #[บรรทัดที่1](37eb38c6-85db-4fb3-8509-9ac2b73f3122) \r\n- Line 2: #[บรรทัดที่2](6ce568f4-aadd-4f7e-bdd9-2c2818c289b3) \r\n- Small text: #[ข้อความเสริม](62de6424-a5eb-4432-b31d-cc4e04266bbc) \r\n\r\nCore text interpretation behavior:\r\n- The user provides only two main lines and one small supporting text.\r\n- Analyze and split the wording intelligently into emphasis groups based on meaning, reading flow, and promotional hierarchy.\r\n- Decide automatically which words should become the dominant focal element, the main headline, the supporting lead-in phrase, the expressive highlight phrase, and the small badge or callout text.\r\n- Do not require the user to pre-label each word.\r\n- Preserve the wording exactly, but choose the styling and grouping intelligently.\r\n\r\nTypography behavior:\r\n- Do not use one single font style for all text.\r\n- Analyze Image B and recreate a multi-font hierarchy based only on the typography style found in the reference.\r\n- Different text groups should use different font personalities depending on their role.\r\n- Match the font mood from Image B: bold block display, rounded inflated display, handwritten note-like style, italic or slanted emphasis, compact headline style, or other visible lettering characteristics found in the reference.\r\n- The goal is to recreate the visual contrast and personality of the typography from Image B, not its layout.\r\n\r\nAutomatic grouping rules:\r\n- If a number appears in the input, treat it as a strong candidate for the most dominant hook element.\r\n- If there is a short English phrase, emotionally charged phrase, or visually punchy phrase, treat it as a likely highlight phrase.\r\n- If there is a short connector word such as “เพื่อ”, “กับ”, “แบบ”, “เรื่อง”, or similar, treat it as a supporting lead-in text.\r\n- The remaining Thai phrase should usually function as the main headline.\r\n- The small text input should be placed as a badge, speech bubble, sticker, or compact callout element.\r\n- If the wording structure differs, still infer the best hierarchy automatically.\r\n\r\nPlacement behavior on Image A:\r\n- Arrange all text directly on Image A only.\r\n- Analyze the background image and place the text where it reads clearly and feels naturally integrated with the scene.\r\n- Choose positions based on empty space, negative space, subject avoidance, visual balance, and readability.\r\n- Do not copy the placement structure of Image B.\r\n- If needed, slightly rebalance the text arrangement to fit the composition of Image A while preserving strong hierarchy.\r\n- The final design must look intentionally designed for the background image, not pasted awkwardly.\r\n\r\nStyling logic by role:\r\n1) Dominant hook element\r\n- Use for the strongest word or number.\r\n- Make it highly eye-catching, large, bold, and visually dominant.\r\n- Use a strong display style with layered outlines and high contrast.\r\n\r\n2) Main headline\r\n- Use for the main Thai phrase.\r\n- Style it as a bold, compact, readable display headline.\r\n- It should support the dominant hook and carry the main meaning.\r\n\r\n3) Supporting lead-in phrase\r\n- Use for short connector words or short supporting phrases.\r\n- Style it smaller than the main highlight but still bold and readable.\r\n- It should visually lead into the highlighted phrase.\r\n\r\n4) Highlight phrase\r\n- Use for the most expressive or emotionally important phrase.\r\n- Make it dynamic, energetic, and more visually expressive than the rest.\r\n- This part may use italic, slanted, script-influenced, or motion-driven display styling if appropriate to match the font mood of Image B.\r\n\r\n5) Small badge text\r\n- Place the small text in a speech bubble, badge, sticker, or compact callout shape.\r\n- Use a different font personality from the headline, often more casual, handwritten, or note-like if that matches Image B.\r\n\r\nGraphic styling:\r\n- Recreate the overall typography language of Image B.\r\n- Use thick outlines, layered borders, sticker-like edges, and soft shadows where appropriate.\r\n- Maintain a playful, polished, high-impact promotional style.\r\n- Use decorative elements only if they support the mood of the typography reference.\r\n- Keep strong readability and high contrast.\r\n\r\nAdaptive behavior:\r\n- Automatically adjust grouping, font size, line breaks, spacing, slant, outline thickness, and supporting shapes based on the text length.\r\n- If the text is short, enlarge it for maximum impact.\r\n- If the text is long, wrap and rebalance it while preserving hierarchy.\r\n- Keep each text group visually distinct in role and font personality.\r\n- Do not flatten everything into one style.\r\n\r\nImage behavior:\r\n- Always use Image A as the final background image.\r\n- Image A can be replaced freely in each generation.\r\n- Use Image B only as a typography-style reference.\r\n- Do not drastically alter the background unless needed for readability.\r\n\r\nImportant instructions:\r\n- Use Image A as the actual final background.\r\n- Use Image B as a typography reference only.\r\n- Do not use Image B as a composition reference.\r\n- Replace all old overlaid text with the new input text.\r\n- Do not require manual labeling of each word group.\r\n- Analyze the wording and assign hierarchy automatically.\r\n- Preserve all input wording exactly, but choose the visual treatment intelligently.\r\n- Arrange the final typography directly on the background image in a balanced, readable, commercially polished way.\r\n- Make the final result look like a polished promotional poster ready for use.","model_name":"nano-banana-2","aspect_ratio":"Auto"},"exposed":{"aspect_ratio":true}},"type":"bananaProNode","position":{"x":300,"y":-255}},{"id":"37eb38c6-85db-4fb3-8509-9ac2b73f3122","data":{"label":"Text Input","nodeName":"บรรทัดที่1","textValue":"","fieldLabel":"ข้อความบรรทัดที่1","placeholder":"Enter text value..."},"type":"textInputNode","position":{"x":-435,"y":-570}},{"id":"86b9a84f-1f63-41dc-b62e-7712e07bf359","data":{"label":"Output","outputType":"video"},"type":"outputNode","position":{"x":735,"y":-135}},{"id":"6ce568f4-aadd-4f7e