n- keep the framing face-cropped or face-obscured similarly to the reference\r\n\r\nFood requirements:\r\n- replace the original dish with the uploaded food image\r\n- preserve the exact identity of the uploaded dish\r\n- do not redesign or reinterpret it into another menu\r\n- keep the real ingredients, colors, textures, proportions, and recognizable appearance of the uploaded dish\r\n- restage the food naturally onto a premium plate presentation similar to the reference\r\n- if the uploaded dish includes side ingredients or sauce, they may be arranged neatly on the plate only if supported by the uploaded image\r\n- make the food look realistic, premium, fresh, and professionally photographed\r\n- preserve realistic texture, gloss, moisture, grill marks, crispness, sauce detail, and natural shadows where appropriate\r\n- do not oversmooth the food\r\n- do not make it look fake, plastic, or overly polished\r\n\r\nPlate and presentation requirements:\r\n- use a clean premium ceramic plate similar in feel to the reference\r\n- keep the plate large and centered\r\n- arrange the food in a balanced fine-dining style\r\n- presentation should feel warm, minimal, elegant, and commercially usable\r\n\r\nLighting and mood requirements:\r\n- match the reference image’s warm moody restaurant lighting\r\n- soft directional light focused on the plate and hands\r\n- gentle shadow depth\r\n- subtle highlights on the food and plate\r\n- slightly dark, blurred background\r\n- overall tone should feel intimate, premium, calm, and appetizing\r\n\r\nImportant constraints:\r\n- absolutely no text, captions, slogans, labels, logos, watermarks, or typography anywhere in the image\r\n- no extra props unless naturally needed\r\n- no unrelated cutlery or table objects distracting from the plate\r\n- no extra dishes\r\n- no collage layout\r\n- no cartoon look\r\n- no distorted hands, arms, plate, or food anatomy\r\n- no fake ingredients not supported by the uploaded food image\r\n\r\nStyle dir